rra(w)</i>.","Italian (southern Sardinia): topographic name or nickname from Sardinian <i>mura</i> ‘mulberry’ or ‘blackberry’."]},{"name":"Muir","meanings":["Scottish: topographic name for someone who lived on a moor, from Older Scots <i>muir</i> ‘moor’ (an expanse of bare, wild upland country). There has been some confusion with   Mure  ."]},{"name":"Morea","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Saverio, Domenic, Ferdinando, Rocco.  Spanish Manuel, Carlos, Cesar, Elvira, Jesus, Mauricio.","Italian (Apulia): from the personal name <i>Morea</i>, originally a habitational name from Morea, the medieval name of the Greek region of Peloponnese, named as the land of mulberry trees, from <i>mōrea</i> ‘mulberry’.","Spanish and Catalan: habitational name from any of the places called Morea, in Badajoz, Navarre, and Lleida provinces."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Mure was born in 1410, in Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom as the son of John Mure. He had at least 1 daughter with Elizabeth Lindsay. He died in 1490, in Dalkeith, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 80."},"et":{"1410–1490":"1410–1490","1391–1452":"1391–1452","1415–1490":"1415–1490","1388–1431":"1388–1431","1415":"1415","1410":"1410","1388":"1388","1431":"1431","1452":"1452","1490":"1490","1391":"1391","Caldwell, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Caldwell, Renfrewshire, Schotland, United Kingdom":"Caldwell, East Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Hawkhead, Renfrewshire, Schotland, United Kingdom":"Hawkhead, Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Dalkeith, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dalkeith, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1410–1490":"1410–1490","1391–1452":"1391–1452","1415–1490":"1415–1490","